article.headline: Campbell 69, Norfolk St. 64
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Jonathan Rodriguez scored 29 points, and Reggie Bishop's 3-point basket with 3:10 remaining sparked a rally that led Campbell to a 69-64 victory over Norfolk State Tuesday night. Norfolk State took a 56-53 lead on Tony Murphy's 3-pointer with 5:13 left. Kyle Vejraska cut the gap to 1 on a jumper at 4:35, and after Murphy missed a 3-point try, Bishop came down the court and gave the Camels (4-6) the lead with 4:10 to go. Rashid Cann's jump shot tied the game for the sixth time at 58 before Bishop responded with the last of his three 3-pointers. Campbell finished the game with eight straight free throws -- four by Vejraska -- and hit 22 of 25 overall. The Camels also shot 52 percent from the floor in the second half, compared to 43 percent for the Spartans (2-7). Vejraska scored 16 points and Bishop had 11 for Campbell. Rodriguez had a game-high 11 rebounds. Murphy led Norfolk State with 18 points despite 6-for-22 shooting. The Spartans took jus six free throws and hit four.
